-- Michael Eisner Says `Highly Unlikely' He Would Take Tribune Chairman Job
-- B y   S a r a h   R a b i l   a n d   B e t t y   L i u
-- 2010-09-22T13:36:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/michael-eisner-says-highly-unlikely-he-would-take-tribune-chairman-job.html
Michael Eisner, the former chief
executive officer of Walt Disney Co., said it’s “highly
unlikely” that he would take the chairman job at Tribune Co.,
the bankrupt newspaper publisher.  Eisner, who owns Tribune debt, spoke in an interview with
Bloomberg Television today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
